  "text": "Alternatively, Segura et al. [CITATION_1] developed an affinity chromatography based on heparin column. Using this approach, up to 94% of proteins impurities and 56% of residual DNA were eliminated while 53% of LV was recovered. Despite these promising data, this kind of chromatography media is not a suitable option for the industry where components of animal origin such as heparin should be precluded.",
